II.   UNION}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Establishment of union\tab 3.\tab It shall be open to the Queen, in the opinion of the Right Honorable Her Majesty's Privy Council, to declare by proclamation that, as of the day designated therein, but not later than six months after the passing of this Act, the provinces of Canada, Nova Scotia and New Brunswick will form one and the same Power under the name of Canada; and from that day on, these three provinces will form, consequently, only one and the same Power under this name. (4)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Interpretation of subsequent provisions of the law\tab 4.\tab Unless otherwise expressly or impliedly, the name of Canada shall mean Canada as constituted under this Act. (5)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Four provinces\tab 5.\tab Canada will be divided into four provinces, called: Ontario, Quebec, Nova Scotia and New Brunswick. (6)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Provinces of Ontario and Quebec\tab 6.\tab The parts of the province of Canada (as existing at the time of the passing of this law) which formerly constituted the respective provinces of Upper and Lower Canada, shall be deemed to be separate and shall form two distinct provinces. The part which was formerly the province of Upper Canada will form the province of Ontario; and the part which constituted the province of Lower Canada will form the province of Quebec.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Provinces of Nova Scotia and New Brunswick\tab 7.\tab The provinces of Nova Scotia and New Brunswick will have the same boundaries assigned to them at the time of the passage of this Act.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Decennial census\tab 8.\tab In the general census of the population of Canada which, by virtue of the present law, shall be carried out in eighteen hundred and seventy-one, and every ten years thereafter, a separate enumeration of the respective populations of the four provinces shall be made.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
