III.  EXECUTIVE POWER}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The Queen is vested with executive power\tab 9.\tab To The Queen shall continue to be and hereby vested with the executive government and authority of Canada.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Application of Governor General Provisions\tab 10.\tab The provisions of this Act relating to the Governor General extend and apply to the Governor General of Canada, or to any Chief Executive or Administrator for the time then, administering the Government of Canada on behalf of the Queen, which regardless of the title under which it may be designated.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Constitution of the Privy Council\tab 11.\tab There shall be, to assist and advise, in the administration of the Government of Canada, a council to be called the Queen's Privy Council for Canada; the persons who will form part of this council will, from time to time, be chosen and appointed by the Governor-General and sworn in as Private Councilors; the members of this council may, from time to time, be removed from office by the Governor General.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Powers conferred on Governor General, in Council or alone\tab 12.\tab or by such governors or lieutenant-governors individually, shall, in so far as they continue to exist and may be exercised, after union, in relation to the government of Canada, vested in the Governor-General and may be by him exercised with the advice or advice and consent of or with the cooperation of the Queen's Privy Council for Canada or any of its members, or by the Governor General individually, as the case may be; but they will be able, (7)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Application of Governor General in Council Provisions\tab 13.\tab The provisions of this Act relating to the Governor General in Council shall be interpreted so as to apply to the Governor General acting on the advice of the Queen's Privy Council for Canada.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The Governor-General authorized to appoint deputies\tab 14.\tab It shall be open to the Queen, if Her Majesty considers it expedient, to authorize the Governor General to appoint from time to time one or more persons, jointly or separately, to act as her Member or Members in any party or parts of Canada, in that capacity, to exercise, during the pleasure of the Governor-General, such powers, duties and functions as the Governor-General deems advisable or necessary for him or to assign to them, subject to the restrictions or instructions given or communicated by the Queen;but the appointment of such deputy or deputies cannot prevent the governor-general himself from exercising the powers, attributions or functions which are conferred on him.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Command of the armies\tab 15.\tab The Queen will continue to be and hereby is given command-in-chief of the Land and Sea Militias and of all military and naval forces in Canada.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Headquarters of the Government of Canada\tab 16.\tab Until the Queen pleases otherwise, Ottawa will be the seat of the Government of Canada.}
