4.\tab the western provinces: Manitoba, British Columbia, Saskatchewan and Alberta;}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
the four divisions shall (subject to revisions to this Act) be equally represented in the Senate, as follows: Ontario by twenty-four senators; Quebec by twenty-four senators; the Maritime Provinces and Prince Edward Island by twenty-four senators, ten of whom represent Nova Scotia, ten represent New Brunswick, and four represent Prince Edward Island; the Western Provinces by twenty-four senators, six of whom represent Manitoba, six from British Columbia, six from Saskatchewan and six from Alberta; the province of Newfoundland will be entitled to be represented in the Senate by six senators; the Yukon Territory and the Northwest Territories are entitled to be represented in the Senate by one Senator each.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
With regard to the province of Quebec, each of the twenty-four senators representing it will be appointed for one of the twenty-four electoral colleges of Lower Canada listed in Schedule A, appended to Chapter I of the revised statutes of Canada. (12)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Qualifications required of senators\tab 23.\tab The qualifications of a Senator will be as follows:}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
1.\tab He must be at least thirty years old;}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
2.\tab He shall be a born subject of the Queen, or a subject of the Queen naturalized by law of the Parliament of Great Britain, or of the Parliament of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland, or of the Legislature of the one of the provinces of Upper Canada, Lower Canada, Canada, Nova Scotia, or New Brunswick, before union, or of the Parliament of Canada, after union;}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
3.\tab He must own, for his own use and benefit, as owner in law or in equity, lands or tenements held in free and common pledge, - or be in good seizure or possession, for his own use and benefit, of lands or tenements. held in freehold or in common in the province for which he is appointed, to the value of four thousand piastres in addition to all annuities, debts, charges,mortgages and royalties which may be attached, due and payable on these buildings or to which they may be assigned;}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
4.\tab All in all, his movable and immovable property must be worth four thousand piastres, in addition to all his debts and obligations;}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
5.\tab He must be domiciled in the province for which he is appointed;}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
6.\tab With regard to the province of Quebec, he must be domiciled or have his land qualification in the electoral college whose representation is assigned to him. (13)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Appointment of Senators\tab 24.\tab The Governor General shall from time to time appoint to the Senate, on behalf of the Queen and by instrument under the Great Seal of Canada, qualified persons; and, subject to the provisions of this law, the persons so mandated will become and will be members of the Senate and senators.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
[Repealed]\tab 25.\tab Repealed. (14)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Number of senators increased in some cases\tab 26.\tab If at any time, on the recommendation of the Governor General, the Queen considers it expedient to order that four or eight members be added to the Senate, the Governor General may, by warrant addressed to four or eight persons (as the case may be) qualified, also representing the four divisions of Canada, add them to the Senate. (15)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Reduction of the Senate to the regular number\tab 27.\tab In the event that the number of senators is thus at any time increased, the Governor-General shall not appoint any person to the Senate, except on such order of the Queen given following the same recommendation, as long as the representation of each of the four divisions of Canada will not revert to the fixed number of twenty-four senators. (16)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Maximum number of senators\tab 28.\tab The number of senators shall at no time exceed one hundred and thirteen. (17)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Senators appointed for life\tab 29.\tab (1) Subject to subsection (2), a Senator holds office in the Senate for his or her life, except as provided in this Act.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Retirement at the age of seventy-five\tab \tab (2) A Senator who is appointed to the Senate after the coming into force of this paragraph shall occupy his place in the Senate, subject to this Act, until he reaches the age of seventy-five years. (18)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Senators can resign from office\tab 30.\tab A senator may, in writing bearing his signature and addressed to the Governor General, resign from office in the Senate, after which his seat shall become vacant.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Cases in which the seats of senators become vacant\tab 31.\tab A Senator's seat will become vacant in each of the following cases:}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
1.\tab If, during two consecutive sessions of the Parliament, he fails to attend the sessions of the Senate;}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
2.\tab If he takes an oath, or subscribes to a declaration or acknowledgment of allegiance, obedience or attachment to a foreign power, or if he performs an act which makes him a subject or a citizen, or confers on him the rights and privileges of a subject or citizen of a foreign power;}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
3.\tab If he is declared in a state of bankruptcy or bankruptcy, or if he has recourse to the benefit of any law concerning bankruptcy, or if he is guilty of concussion;}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
4.\tab If he is afflicted with treason or convicted of felony, or of any infamous crime;}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
5.\tab If it ceases to have the qualification based on property or domicile; but a Senator shall not be deemed to have lost the qualification based on domicile by the sole fact of his residence at the seat of the Government of Canada while he occupies an office under that Government which requires his presence there.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Appointment in case of vacancy\tab 32.\tab When a seat in the Senate becomes vacant by resignation, death or any other cause, the Governor General will fill the vacancy by issuing a warrant to some capable and qualified person.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Questions about qualifications and vacancies, etc.\tab 33.\tab If any question arises concerning the qualifications of a senator or a vacancy in the Senate, that question shall be heard and decided by the Senate.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Speaker of the Senate\tab 34.\tab The Governor General may, from time to time, by instrument under the Great Seal of Canada, appoint a Senator as speaker of the Senate, and remove him or her and appoint another in his stead. (19)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Quorum of the Senate\tab 35.\tab Until the Parliament of Canada orders otherwise, the presence of at least fifteen Senators, including the speaker, will be required to constitute an assembly of the Senate in the exercise of its functions.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Voting in the Senate\tab 36.\tab Questions raised in the Senate will be decided by a majority of votes, and in all cases, the speaker will have the right to vote; when the votes are equally divided, the decision will be deemed to have been rendered in the negative.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
 }
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
THE HOUSE OF COMMONS}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Constitution of the House of Commons\tab 37.\tab The House of Commons shall, subject to the provisions of this Act, be composed of two hundred and ninety-five members, of whom ninety-nine shall represent Ontario, seventy-five Quebec, eleven Nova Scotia, ten the New -Brunswick, fourteen Manitoba, thirty-two British Columbia, four Prince Edward Island, twenty-six Alberta, fourteen Saskatchewan, seven Newfoundland, one the Yukon Territory and two Northwest Territories. (20)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Convocation of the House of Commons\tab 38.\tab The Governor General will from time to time convene the House of Commons on behalf of the Queen by instrument under the Great Seal of Canada.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Exclusion of Senators from the House of Commons\tab 39.\tab A senator cannot be elected, nor sit, nor vote as a member of the House of Commons.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Electoral districts of the four provinces\tab 40.\tab Until the Parliament of Canada orders otherwise, the provinces of Ontario, Quebec, Nova Scotia and New Brunswick will, as regards the election of members of the House of Commons, be divided. into electoral districts as follows:}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
1. Ontario}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The province of Ontario shall be divided into counties, divisions of counties ( Ridings ), cities, parts of cities and towns as listed in the first schedule to this Act; each of these divisions shall form an electoral district, and each district designated in this annex shall be entitled to elect one member.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
2. Quebec}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The province of Quebec will be divided into sixty-five electoral districts, comprising the sixty-five electoral divisions into which Lower Canada is currently divided by virtue of chapter two of the Consolidated Statutes of Canada, and chapter seventy-five of the Statutes Recast for Lower Canada, and of the Act of the Province of Canada of the Twenty-Third Year of the Reign of Her Majesty the Queen, Chapter I, or of any other law amending them and in force at the time of the 'union, in such a way that each electoral division constitutes, for the purposes of this law, an electoral district having the right to elect a member.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
3. Nova Scotia}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Each of Nova Scotia's eighteen counties will form an electoral district. The County of Halifax will be entitled to elect two members and each of the other counties one member.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
4. New Brunswick}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Each of the fourteen counties of which New Brunswick is made up, including the city and county of St. John, will form an electoral district. The city of St. John will also constitute an electoral district on its own. Each of these fifteen electoral districts will have the right to elect one member. (21)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Continuation of current election laws\tab 41.\tab Until the Parliament of Canada orders otherwise, all laws in force in the various provinces, at the time of the union, relating to the following matters or none of them, namely: eligibility or ineligibility of candidates or members of the chamber of assembly or legislative assembly in the various provinces, the voters in the elections of these members, the oaths required of the voters, the officer-rapporteurs, their powers and their duties, the mode of proceeding to the elections, as long as they can last,the decision of the contested elections and the incidental procedures thereto, the vacancies of the seats in parliament and the execution of new writs in the cases of vacations occasioned by causes other than the dissolution, will apply respectively to the elections of the members sent to the House of Commons by these various provinces.causes other than dissolution, shall apply respectively to the elections of the members sent to the House of Commons by these various provinces.causes other than dissolution, shall apply respectively to the elections of the members sent to the House of Commons by these various provinces.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
But, until the Parliament of Canada orders otherwise, at each election of a member of the House of Commons for the District of Algoma, in addition to those persons entitled to vote under the law of the Province of Canada, any English subject of the male sex, twenty-one years of age or over and holding fire and place, shall have the right to vote. (22)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
[Repealed]\tab 42.\tab Repealed. (23)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
[Repealed]\tab 43.\tab Repealed. (24)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Speaker of the House of Commons\tab 44.\tab The House of Commons, at its first meeting after a general election, will, with all possible speed, elect one of its members as speaker.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
When the office of speaker becomes vacant\tab 45.\tab In the event of a vacancy in the office of speaker, by death, resignation or other cause, the House of Commons will proceed, with all possible speed, to the election of another of its members as speaker.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The speaker takes the chair\tab 46.\tab The speaker will preside over all sittings of the House of Commons.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Provided in the event of the absence of the speaker\tab 47.\tab Until the Parliament of Canada orders otherwise, if the speaker for any reason leaves the chair of the House of Commons for forty-eight consecutive hours, the chamber may elect another of its members to act as speaker; the member thus elected shall have and exercise, during the absence of the speaker, all the powers, privileges and attributions of the latter. (25)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Quorum of the House of Commons\tab 48.\tab The presence of at least twenty members of the House of Commons will be necessary to constitute an assembly of the chamber in the exercise of its powers; for this purpose, the speaker will be counted as a member.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Voting in the House of Commons\tab 49.\tab Questions raised in the House of Commons will be decided by a majority of votes, except that of the speaker, but when the votes are equally divided, and in this case only, the speaker may vote.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Duration of the House of Commons\tab 50.\tab The term of the House of Commons shall be only five years, from the day of the report of the writs of election, unless it is earlier dissolved by the Governor General. (26)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Electoral revisions\tab 51.\tab (1) Upon the entry into force of this paragraph and, thereafter, at the end of each decennial census, the number of deputies and the representation of the provinces in the House of Commons shall be revised according to the powers conferred and the terms of time or otherwise fixed from time to time by the Parliament of Canada, taking into account the following rules:}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
