Lieutenant-governors of the provinces\tab 58.\tab There will be, for each province, an officer called Lieutenant Governor, who will be appointed by the Governor General in Council by instrument under the Great Seal of Canada.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Term of office of lieutenant governors\tab 59.\tab The Lieutenant Governor will remain in office during the pleasure of the Governor General; but any lieutenant-governor appointed after the commencement of the first session of the Parliament of Canada, may not be dismissed during the five years which follow his appointment, unless there is cause; and this cause must be communicated to him in writing within one month after the order decreeing his dismissal has been issued, and also be communicated by message to the Senate and to the House of Commons in the course of}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Lieutenant Governors' Salaries\tab 60.\tab The salaries of lieutenant governors will be fixed and paid by the Parliament of Canada. (30)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Oaths, etc., of the Lieutenant Governor\tab 61.\tab Each lieutenant-governor, before entering into the exercise of his functions, shall take and subscribe before the Governor-General or any person authorized thereto by him, the oaths of allegiance and office taken by the Governor-General.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Application of provisions relating to Lieutenant Governor\tab 62.\tab The provisions of this Act relating to the lieutenant governor extend and apply to the lieutenant governor of each province or to any other chief executive or administrator for the time then administering the government of the province, regardless of the title under which it is designated.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Ontario and Quebec Executive Councils\tab 63.\tab The executive council of Ontario and Quebec shall be composed of such persons as the Lieutenant Governor deems appropriate from time to time to appoint, and in the first place, of the following officers, namely: the Attorney General, the Secretary and Registrar of the province, the treasurer of the province, the commissioner of crown lands, and the commissioner of agriculture and public works, and - in the province of Quebec - the speaker of the legislative council, and the solicitor general. (31)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Executive Government of Nova Scotia and New Brunswick\tab 64.\tab The constitution of executive authority in each of the provinces of New Brunswick and Nova Scotia shall continue, subject to the provisions of this Act, to be that in existence at the time of union, until such time as it is established. be amended under the authority of this law. (32)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Powers conferred on the Lieutenant-Governor of Ontario or Quebec, in council or alone\tab 65.\tab or by such governors or lieutenant-governors individually, will be - to the extent that they may be exercised after the union, in relation to the government of Ontario and Quebec respectively - conferred on the lieutenant-governor of Ontario and Quebec, respectively, and may be exercised by him, with the advice or opinion and consent or with the cooperation of the respective executive councils or any of their members, or by the Lieutenant-Governor individually, as the case may be; but they will be able,(33)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Application of Lieutenant Governors in Council Provisions\tab 66.\tab The provisions of this Act relating to the Lieutenant Governor in Council shall be interpreted as applying to the Lieutenant Governor of the Province acting on the advice of his Executive Council.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Administration in absence, etc., of Lieutenant Governor\tab 67.\tab The Governor General in Council may, from time to time, appoint an administrator to act as Lieutenant Governor during the latter's absence, illness or other incapacity.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Provincial government seats\tab 68.\tab Until the executive government of a province orders otherwise, with respect to such province, the seats of provincial government shall be as follows, namely: for Ontario, the city of Toronto; for Quebec, the city of Quebec; for Nova Scotia, the city of Halifax; and for New Brunswick, the city of Fredericton.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
