\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Quebec Legislature\tab 71.\tab There will be, for Quebec, a legislature composed of the lieutenant-governor and two chambers called the legislative council of Quebec and the legislative assembly of Quebec. (35)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Constitution of the legislative council\tab 72.\tab The legislative council of Quebec will be composed of twenty-four members, who will be appointed by the Lieutenant-Governor in the name of the Queen, by instrument under the Great Seal of Quebec, and must each represent one of the twenty-four colleges. constituencies of Lower Canada mentioned in this law; they shall be appointed for life, unless the legislature of Quebec orders otherwise under the authority of this law.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Qualifications required of legislative counsel\tab 73.\tab The qualifications of legislative counsel for Quebec will be the same as those of senators for Quebec.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Cases in which the seats of legislative counsel become vacant\tab 74.\tab The office of legislative counsel for Quebec will become vacant in cases, mutatis mutandis , where that of senator may become so.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Vacation\tab 75.\tab In the event of a vacancy in the Legislative Council of Quebec, by resignation, death or other cause, the Lieutenant-Governor, in the name of the Queen, will appoint, by instrument under the Great Seal of Quebec, a person capable and having the requisite qualifications for the to fill.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Questions about vacations, etc.\tab 76.\tab If any question arises concerning the qualifications of a legislative councilor of Quebec or a vacancy in the legislative council of Quebec, it will be heard and decided by the legislative council.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Speaker of the Legislative Council\tab 77.\tab The Lieutenant-Governor may, from time to time, by instrument under the Great Seal of Quebec, appoint a member of the legislative council of Quebec as orator of that body, and also dismiss him and appoint another in his place.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Quorum of the Legislative Council\tab 78.\tab Until the legislature of Quebec orders otherwise, the presence of at least ten members of the legislative council, including the speaker, will be necessary to constitute an assembly of the council in the exercise of its functions.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Voting in the legislative council of Quebec\tab 79.\tab Questions raised in the legislative council of Quebec will be decided by a majority of votes, and, in all cases, the speaker will have the right to vote; when the votes are equally divided, the decision will be deemed to have been rendered in the negative.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Constitution of the legislative assembly of Quebec\tab 80.\tab The legislative assembly of Quebec will be composed of sixty-five members, who will be elected to represent the sixty-five electoral divisions or districts of Lower Canada, mentioned in this law, except for any modification which the legislature of Quebec may make; but no bill to the effect of modifying the boundaries of the electoral divisions or districts enumerated in the second schedule of this law may be presented to the lieutenant-governor of Quebec, for his sanction, unless he was passed to his second and third readings in the legislative assembly with the assistance of a majority of members representing all such divisions or electoral districts; and sanction shall not be given to any Bill of this nature unless an address has been presented to the Lieutenant Governor by the Legislative Assembly declaring that such Bill has been so passed.(36)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
