\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Choice of judges in Quebec\tab 98.\tab The judges of the courts of Quebec will be chosen from among the members of the bar of that province.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Term of office of judges\tab 99.\tab (1) Subject to subsection (2) of this section, judges of the superior courts shall remain in office during good conduct, but they may be removed from office by the Governor General at an address of the Senate and the House of Commons.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Termination of functions at the age of 75\tab \tab (2) A judge of a superior court appointed before or after the coming into force of this section shall cease to hold office upon reaching the age of seventy-five years, or upon coming into force. force of this article if, at that time, he has already reached the said age. (52)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Salaries, etc. judges\tab 100.\tab Salaries, allowances and pensions of judges of superior, district and county courts (except audit courts in Nova Scotia and New Brunswick) and Admiralty courts, when judges of the latter are then employees, will be fixed and paid by the Parliament of Canada. (53)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
General Court of Appeal, etc.\tab 101.\tab The Parliament of Canada may, notwithstanding any provision to the contrary set forth in this Act, when the occasion requires it, adopt measures to create, maintain and organize a general court of appeal for Canada, and establish tribunals for the better administration of the laws of Canada. (54)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
