\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
VIII.   REVENUES; DEBTS; ASSETS; TAX}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Creation of a consolidated revenue fund\tab 102.\tab All rights and revenues which the respective legislatures of Canada, Nova Scotia and New Brunswick, before and at the time of the union, had the power to appropriate, except those reserved by this Act to the legislatures respective provinces, or which will be collected by them in accordance with the special powers conferred on them by this law, shall form a consolidated revenue fund to be appropriate for the public service of Canada in the manner and subject to the charges provided for by this law.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Collection costs, etc.\tab 103.\tab The Consolidated Revenue Fund of Canada shall be permanently encumbered with the fees, charges and expenses incurred in collecting, administering and collecting it, which shall constitute the first charge on this fund and may be subject to such review and hearing as may be ordered by the Governor General. in council until parliament provides otherwise.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Interest on provincial public debts\tab 104.\tab The annual interest on the public debts of the various provinces of Canada, Nova Scotia and New Brunswick, at the time of the union, will constitute the second charge on the consolidated revenue fund of Canada.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Salary of the Governor General\tab 105.\tab Until modified by the Parliament of Canada, the salary of the Governor-General shall be ten thousand louis, sterling rate of the United Kingdom of Great Britain and Ireland; this sum will be paid out of the consolidated revenue fund of Canada and will constitute the third charge on this fund. (55)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Use of consolidated fund\tab 106.\tab Subject to the various payments with which the consolidated revenue fund of Canada is encumbered by this law, this fund will be appropriated by the Parliament of Canada for the public service.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Transfer of values, etc.\tab 107.\tab All funds, cash in hand, balances in the hands of the bankers and securities belonging to each province at the time of the union, except the exceptions set out in this Act, shall become the property of Canada and shall be deducted from the amount of the debts. respective provinces during the union.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Transfer of the properties listed in the annex\tab 108.\tab The public works and property of each province, enumerated in the third schedule of this law, shall belong to Canada.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Ownership of land, mines, etc.\tab 109.\tab All lands, mines, minerals and royal reserves belonging to the different provinces of Canada, Nova Scotia and New Brunswick at the time of union, and all sums of money then due or payable for such lands, mines, minerals and royal reserves, will belong to the various provinces of Ontario, Quebec, Nova Scotia and New Brunswick, in which they are located and situated, or payable, always remaining subject to the charges with which they are encumbered, as well as to all interests other than those which the province may have. (56)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Provincial assets and debts\tab 110.\tab All of the assets inherent in the portions of the public debt assumed by each province will belong to that province.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Liability for provincial debts\tab 111.\tab Canada will be responsible for the debts and obligations of each province existing at the time of union.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Liability for debts of Ontario and Quebec\tab 112.\tab The provinces of Ontario and Quebec will be jointly responsible to Canada for the excess debt (if any) of the province of Canada, if, at the time of union, it exceeds sixty-two million five hundred thousand piastres, and required to pay interest on this excess at the rate of five per cent per annum.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Active in Ontario and Quebec\tab 113.\tab The assets enumerated in the fourth schedule of this law, belonging, at the time of the union, to the province of Canada, will be the property of Ontario and Quebec jointly.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Nova Scotia Debt\tab 114.\tab Nova Scotia will be liable to Canada for the excess (if any) of its public debt if, at the time of the union, it exceeds eight million piastres, and liable to pay the interest on this excess. at the rate of five percent per year. (57)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
New Brunswick debt\tab 115.\tab New Brunswick will be responsible to Canada for the excess (if any) of its public debt, if at the time of the union, it exceeds seven million piastres, and required to pay the interest on this excess. at the rate of five percent per year.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Interest payments to Nova Scotia and New Brunswick\tab 116.\tab In the event that, at the time of the union, the public debts of Nova Scotia and New Brunswick are respectively less than eight million and seven million piastres, these provinces shall each be entitled to receive from the Government of Canada, in semi-annual and advance payments, interest at the rate of five per cent per annum on the difference which will exist between the actual figure of their respective debts and the amount thus fixed.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Provincial public property\tab 117.\tab The various provinces shall respectively retain all their public property which is not otherwise provided for in this law, subject to the right of Canada to take the lands or public property which it will need for the fortifications or the defense of the country.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
[Repealed]\tab 118.\tab Repealed. (58)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Additional grant in New Brunswick\tab 119.\tab New Brunswick will receive from Canada, in semi-annual and advance payments, for a period of ten years from the union, an additional grant of sixty-three thousand piastres per year; but as long as the public debt of that province remains below seven million piastres, it will be deducted from this sum of sixty-three thousand piastres, an amount equal to the interest at five per cent per annum on such difference. (59)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Form of payments\tab 120.\tab All payments prescribed by this Act, or intended to extinguish obligations contracted under a law of the Provinces of Canada, Nova Scotia and New Brunswick respectively and assumed by Canada, shall be made, until as otherwise ordered by the Parliament of Canada, in such form and manner as the Governor General in Council may from time to time prescribe.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Canadian manufactures, etc.\tab 121.\tab All articles of the vintage, origin or manufacture of any of the provinces will, from the date of the union, be admitted duty free in each of the other provinces.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Continuation of customs and excise laws\tab 122.\tab The customs and excise laws of each province shall remain in force, subject to the provisions of this Act, until amended by the Parliament of Canada. (60)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Export and import between two provinces\tab 123.\tab In the event that customs duties are, at the time of the union, taxable on articles, commodities or goods, in two provinces, these articles, commodities or goods may, after the union, be imported from the one of these two provinces in the other, on proof of payment of the customs duties imposed on them in the province from which they are exported, and on payment of any surplus customs duties (if any) of which they can be minted in the province where they are imported. (61)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Timber Taxes in New Brunswick\tab 124.\tab Nothing in this Act shall prejudice the privilege guaranteed in New Brunswick to levy on timber the rights established by Chapter Fifteen of Title Three of the Revised Statutes of New Brunswick, or by any law amending it before or after l union, but not increasing the number of these rights; and lumber from provinces other than New Brunswick will not be subject to these duties. (62)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Public lands, etc., exempt from taxes\tab 125.\tab No land or property belonging to Canada or to any particular province will be subject to taxation.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Consolidated Provincial Revenue Fund\tab 126.\tab The rights and revenues which the respective legislatures of Canada, Nova Scotia and New Brunswick had, before the union, the power to appropriate, and which are, by this Act, reserved to the governments or legislatures of the provinces respective ones, and all the rights and revenues collected by them in accordance with the special powers conferred on them by this law, will form in each province a consolidated revenue fund which will be appropriate for the public service of the province.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch
