\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Oath of allegiance, etc.\tab 128.\tab Members of the Senate or of the House of Commons of Canada shall, before entering into the exercise of their functions, lend and subscribe, before the Governor-General or any person so authorized by him, and similarly, the members of the legislative council or of the legislative assembly of a province shall, before entering into the exercise of their functions, take and subscribe before the lieutenant-governor of the province or any person authorized thereto by him, the oath of allegiance set out in the fifth schedule to this law; and the members of the Senate of Canada and of the legislative council of Quebec must also, before entering the}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Current laws, courts and officials will continue to exist, etc.\tab 129.\tab Except as otherwise provided by this Act, all laws in force in Canada, Nova Scotia or New Brunswick, at the time of union, all courts of civil and criminal jurisdiction, all commissions, powers and authorities having legal force, and all judicial, administrative and ministerial officers in existence in those provinces at the time of the union, will continue to exist in the provinces of Ontario, Quebec, Nova Scotia and New Brunswick respectively, as if the union had not taken place; but they will be able,(64)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Officials transferred to the service of Canada\tab 130.\tab Until the Parliament of Canada orders otherwise, all the officers of the various provinces having to fulfill duties relating to matters other than those falling within the categories of subjects assigned exclusively by this law to the legislatures of the provinces, shall be officers. of Canada and will continue to fulfill the duties of their respective offices under the same obligations and penalties as if the union had not taken place. (65)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Appointment of new officers\tab 131.\tab Until the Parliament of Canada orders otherwise, the Governor General in Council may from time to time appoint such officers as he considers necessary or advisable for the effective carrying out of this Act.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Obligations arising from treaties\tab 132.\tab The Parliament and the Government of Canada will have all the powers necessary to fulfill towards foreign countries, as a portion of the British Empire, the obligations of Canada or of any of its provinces, arising from treaties concluded between the Empire and these countries. foreigners.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
Optional and compulsory use of French and English\tab 133.\tab In the chambers of the Parliament of Canada and the chambers of the legislature of Quebec, the use of the French language or the English language, in the debates, will be optional; but in the drafting of the respective archives, minutes and journals of these chambers, the use of these two languages \u8203\'3f\u8203\'3fwill be compulsory; and in any pleadings or pleadings before the courts or emanating from the courts of Canada which will be established under the authority of this law, and before all the courts or emanating from the courts of Quebec, it may also be done use, at option, of one or the other of these languages.}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049{\rtlch \ltrch\loch
The laws of the Parliament of Canada and the Legislature of Quebec must be printed and published in these two languages. (66)}
\par \pard\plain \s0\nowidctlpar\hyphpar0\cf0\kerning1\dbch\af8\langfe2052\dbch\af6\afs24\alang1081\loch\f3\hich\af3\fs24\lang1049\rtlch \ltrch\loch

